{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βωμός</b>, ὁ, <br /> (βαίνω) <b>raised platform, stand</b>, for chariots, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.441 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>base</b> of a statue, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.100: but, \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> mostly, <b>altar with a base</b>, ἱερὸς β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.305, etc.; πρὸς βωμῷ σφαγείς 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 305; βωμὸς ἀρῆς φυγάσιν ῥῦμα [prev. author] “Supp.” 84 (Lyric poetry); βωμῶν ἀπείργειν τινά [prev. author] “Ch.” 293; ἀγυιεὺς β. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 370 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of suppliants, ποτὶ βωμὸν ἵζεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.334 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; βωμοῖσι προσῆσθαι, προσπεσόντα βωμῷ καθῆσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 16, “OC” 1158; βωμὸν ἵζειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1314 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also in Prose, β. ἱδρύσασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.142, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 322a; ἱζόμενοι ἐπὶ τὸν β. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.108; ἐπὶ βωμῶν καθέζεσθαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> later, <b>tomb, cairn,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" epigram Gr. 319. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> title of poems by Dosiades and Besantinus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 15.26and25, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Lex.” 25. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>altar-shaped cake,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 2.1651B,C, 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 6.76. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> Ζεὺς Βωμός, probably a Syrian god, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hermes” 37.118 (from Syria). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> <b>central fire</b> in the system of Philolaus, <i>accusative</i> to [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Placita Philosophorum” 2.7.7. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__8</b></Level3> in <i>plural</i>, ={ἔμβολοι}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1041","accentedUnicode":"βωμός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0939","matchingForm":"βάσις","stepTransliteration":"basis","gloss":"foot","_zh_tw_Gloss":"腳","_es_Gloss":"pie","_zh_Gloss":"脚"}],"shortDef":"altar","mediumDef":"<i>primarily</i> <b>a slightly-elevated spot, base, pedestal;</b> hence, <b>an altar, high place</b> <ref='Act.17.23'>Acts 17:23</ref>*","stepGloss":"altar","stepTransliteration":"bōmos","count":1,"_es_Definition":"altar","_zh_tw_Definition":"祭壇 (徒 17:23)","_zh_Definition":"祭坛 (徒 17:23)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"bàn thờ.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一座壇","_es_Gloss":"altar ","_zh_Gloss":"一座坛"}]}